<item>
            <title>[AMQ-1748] Deadlock when TempUsage limit reached</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-1748</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a SystemUsage limit is set on TempUsage, and that limit is reached, that queue enters a state of deadlock where messages need to be removed so new ones can be added, but they can&apos;t be removed because the objects are locked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have a patch attached to this issue where the synchronization in StoreQueueCursor and FilePendingMessageCursor is reworked to get around this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Tested on Linux&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
